  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CHAI Phase V: Transforming lives of the rural poor in Tea communities of Assam &amp; Darjeeling, India and Alta Verapaz, Guatemala</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Families: Children, women, etc.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal: Improve the lives of 17,000 people in and adjacent to tea and botanical growing communities through improved water and sanitation, youth leadership and economic development activities.
1.        Opportunities for youth engagement in all aspects of CHAI including (but not limited to) educational and income generation opportunities. 
2.        Income generating opportunities that provide alternative sources of employment in origin communities, improving family incomes. 
3.        Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) improvements that provide better access to clean drinking water and significantly improve public health by reducing the incidence of waterborne diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through continued support from Starbucks Foundation, Tazo Tea, Mercy Corps and Indian tea Companies over the last decade, CHAI INDIA has provided opportunities for tea communities in Assam and Darjeeling to improve their socio-economic and health conditions. Mercy Corps is committed to continuing this support and further expand opportunities to serve the most vulnerable communities in the areas where we work. The tea workers continue to live in labor intensive and challenging conditions in the tea gardens where access to basic health services and opportunities to provide for their families remain daily challenges. As rising population rates continue, the need and demand for other livelihood opportunities remains high with limited opportunities for advancement. Mercy Corps proposes to work with the Starbucks Foundation on continuing the CHAI partnership to improve the quality of life now and into the future of these families.</narrative>
  </description>
